                    _t('Patterns of Imagery', 'Extended or repeated imagery (imagery patterns) creates thematic emphasis; a poem consistently using images of cold and darkness is making a statement through that accumulation.', 'Identifying a pattern is more analytically powerful than identifying a single image — the pattern suggests intentionality and thematic significance.', 'AP®: identify dominant imagery patterns and explain what they collectively reveal about the poem\'s meaning.'),
                    _t('Concrete vs. Abstract', 'Literary poetry grounds abstract ideas (love, mortality, justice) in concrete, sensory images — this is what makes poetry more powerful than philosophical statement.', '"My love is like a red, red rose" (concrete image) communicates differently than "My love is beautiful and pure" (abstract statement).', 'AP®: analyze how a poem uses concrete imagery to explore abstract themes.'),
